Epic name custom field is only available for the Epic issue type. It would be useful to have it available for all the other issue types to perform searches on the issue navigator:

{code:sql}
"Epic Name" = "Epic 1"
{code}

This would retrieve all the issues that are part of Epic 1. The Epic link custom field could provides a similar functionality, however, customers usually link Stories to Epics based on the Epic Name, not the Epic Link. Using the Epic Name for that purpose would make things easier when performing searches in the Issue Navigator.

As of now, it's easy to add an Issue to a Sprint and never realize that it's being blocked by another one. It would be handy if:
- blocked Issues had a notifying icon on their card (as in Classic Boards - GHS-48);
- a note would be displayed then a blocked Issue is added to a Sprint, reminding the user that they might want to resolve the blocking one first.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-9013].
  {panel}

Opening the Detail View can cause column header text to wrap to multiple lines which can obscure the top of issues if the backlog is tall enough to scroll.

We probably need to call the resize function (which we call on viewport resize) when the Detail View opens/closes.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-8949].
  {panel}

When trying to use the Version Report, I was unable to select my latest version because the drop down list is too long and doesn't allow to go down in the list.

I tried to scroll, to go down with the mouse and to use Pg Down.

*Workaround*

Use the following as a bookmarklet:
{noformat}
javascript:(function(){var dd = document.getElementById('ghx-items-trigger_drop'); 
if(dd){dd.style.top=dd.style.bottom=0;dd.style.overflowY="scroll"}})();
{noformat}
Create a new bookmark with the code above as the URL, and click on such bookmark whenever you're looking at the Report tab in GreenHopper with the Sprint selection list open. It will automagically scroll to the top of the dropdown, and add scrolling capabilities to it.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
